text: Nizhny Sardyk () is a rural locality (a village) in Tatar-Ulkanovsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 209 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 21 km from Tuymazy, 9 km from Tatar-Ulkanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Nizhny Sardyk
